<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 -
        Assembly - High and Low Shifter Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>High and Low Shifter Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grease all O-ring seals. Use a light coat of lithium-based grease (Meritor specification
                0-688). Refer to Figure 53 for shifter component arrangement.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install O-rings on the inside diameter and outside diameter of the inner piston. Install the
                inner shift piston and snap ring onto the shift shaft (Figure 54).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install O-rings on the inside diameter and outside diameter of the outer piston. Install the
                outer shift piston.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303553" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303553.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Shifter Component Arrangement</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. LOW RANGE PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. NEUTRAL PORT (MTC-4208 AND -4210 ONLY)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HIGH RANGE PORT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303554" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303554.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Install Inner Shift Piston</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. INNER SHIFT PISTON</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer shift piston outer snap ring onto the shift shaft (Figure 55).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a 1/8-inch (3 mm) bead of Loctite&#174; 277 sealant to the first three threads of the
                shift cylinder.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the high and low shift cylinder. Tighten the cylinder to 85-95 lb-ft (115-129 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear output shaft seal using seal driver R4422402 (Meritor Kit No. 4454). Drive
                the seal until it is fully seated.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">MTC-4208 and -4210 transfer cases only: Install the rear output shaft yoke, washer and yoke
                nut. Tighten the 700-900 lb-ft (949-1220 Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303555" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303555.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Install Outer Shift Piston</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OUTER SHIFT PISTON</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
